line_1: THE glow-worm scribblers of a feeble age,
line_2: Pale twinklers of an hour provoke my rage:

line_1: Pale twinklers of an hour provoke my rage:
line_2: THE glow-worm scribblers of a feeble age,

line_1: In each dark hedge we start an insect fire,
line_2: Which lives by night, and must at dawn expire;

line_1: Which lives by night, and must at dawn expire;
line_2: In each dark hedge we start an insect fire,

line_1: Yet such their number that their specks combine,
line_2: And the unthinking vulgar swear they shine.

line_1: And the unthinking vulgar swear they shine.
line_2: Yet such their number that their specks combine,

line_1: Poets are prodigies so greatly rare,
line_2: They seem the talks of heav'n, and built with care:

line_1: They seem the talks of heav'n, and built with care:
line_2: Poets are prodigies so greatly rare,

line_1: Like suns, unquench'd, unrival'd and sublime,
line_2: They roll, immortal, o'er the wastes of time:

line_1: They roll, immortal, o'er the wastes of time:
line_2: Like suns, unquench'd, unrival'd and sublime,

line_1: Ages in vain close round and snatch in fame;
line_2: High over all still shines the Poet's name!

line_1: High over all still shines the Poet's name!
line_2: Ages in vain close round and snatch in fame;

line_1: Lords of a life that scorns the bounds of breath,
line_2: They stretch existence and defy stern death.

line_1: They stretch existence and defy stern death.
line_2: Lords of a life that scorns the bounds of breath,

line_1: Glory and shame are theirs — they plant renown,
line_2: Or shade the Monarch's by the Muse's crown:

line_1: Or shade the Monarch's by the Muse's crown:
line_2: Glory and shame are theirs — they plant renown,

line_1: To say Augustus reign'd when Virgil shin'd,
line_2: Does honour to the lord of half mankind.

line_1: Does honour to the lord of half mankind.
line_2: To say Augustus reign'd when Virgil shin'd,

line_1: So when three thousand years have wan'd away,
line_2: And POPE is said t' have liv'd when GEORGE bore sway,

line_1: And POPE is said t' have liv'd when GEORGE bore sway,
line_2: So when three thousand years have wan'd away,

line_1: Millions shall lend the King the Poet's fame,
line_2: And bless implicit the supported name.

line_1: And bless implicit the supported name.
line_2: Millions shall lend the King the Poet's fame,

line_1: FROM every Muse and every art thy own,
line_2: Thy bow'rs our theatres, thy mind our throne!

line_1: Thy bow'rs our theatres, thy mind our throne!
line_2: FROM every Muse and every art thy own,

line_1: Hail! to thy virtues manumiz'd from state;
line_2: Hail! to thy leisure to be wisely great.

line_1: Hail! to thy leisure to be wisely great.
line_2: Hail! to thy virtues manumiz'd from state;

line_1: Fetter'd by duties and to forms enslav'd,
line_2: How timely have thy years a remnant sav'd!

line_1: How timely have thy years a remnant sav'd!
line_2: Fetter'd by duties and to forms enslav'd,

line_1: To taste that freedom which thy sword maintain'd,
line_2: And lead in letter'd ease, a life unpain'd:

line_1: And lead in letter'd ease, a life unpain'd:
line_2: To taste that freedom which thy sword maintain'd,

line_1: So Scipio (Carthage fall'n) resign'd his plume,
line_2: And smil'd at the forgetfulness of Rome.

line_1: And smil'd at the forgetfulness of Rome.
line_2: So Scipio (Carthage fall'n) resign'd his plume,

line_1: O greatly bless'd! whose evening sweetest shines,
line_2: And, in unclouded slowness, calm declines!

line_1: And, in unclouded slowness, calm declines!
line_2: O greatly bless'd! whose evening sweetest shines,

line_1: While free reflection with reverted eye,
line_2: Wan'd from hot noon-tide and a troubled sky,

line_1: Wan'd from hot noon-tide and a troubled sky,
line_2: While free reflection with reverted eye,

line_1: Divides life well: the largest part, long known
line_2: Thy country's claim; the last and best thy own.

line_1: Thy country's claim; the last and best thy own.
line_2: Divides life well: the largest part, long known

line_1: Here while detach'd, thy self-supported soul
line_2: Resumes dominion and escapes controul;

line_1: Resumes dominion and escapes controul;
line_2: Here while detach'd, thy self-supported soul

line_1: Moves with a grandeur, monarchs wish in vain,
line_2: Above all fears, storms, dangers, hopes or pain;

line_1: Above all fears, storms, dangers, hopes or pain;
line_2: Moves with a grandeur, monarchs wish in vain,

line_1: A glance sometimes from thy safe summit show,
line_2: And see the dusty world look dim below:

line_1: And see the dusty world look dim below:
line_2: A glance sometimes from thy safe summit show,

line_1: Thro' the dark throng discern huge slaves of pride
line_2: Should'ring unheeded Happiness aside;

line_1: Should'ring unheeded Happiness aside;
line_2: Thro' the dark throng discern huge slaves of pride

line_1: Thwarted and push'd and lab'ring into name,
line_2: And dignify'd with all the dirt of fame;

line_1: And dignify'd with all the dirt of fame;
line_2: Thwarted and push'd and lab'ring into name,

line_1: Then with a smile superior, turn away,
line_2: And lop th' exub'rance of some straggling spray;

line_1: And lop th' exub'rance of some straggling spray;
line_2: Then with a smile superior, turn away,

line_1: Wind thro' thy mazes to serene delight,
line_2: And from the bursting bubbles shade thy sight.

line_1: And from the bursting bubbles shade thy sight.
line_2: Wind thro' thy mazes to serene delight,

line_1: Yet where thou shin'st, like heav'n behind a cloud,
line_2: Moving like light, all piercing, tho' not loud;

line_1: Moving like light, all piercing, tho' not loud;
line_2: Yet where thou shin'st, like heav'n behind a cloud,

line_1: The Muse shall find thee in thy blest retreat,
line_2: And breathe this honest wish at Cobham's feet:

line_1: And breathe this honest wish at Cobham's feet:
line_2: The Muse shall find thee in thy blest retreat,

line_1: Fresh as thy lakes, may all thy pleasures flow!
line_2: And breezy like thy groves, thy passions blow!

line_1: And breezy like thy groves, thy passions blow!
line_2: Fresh as thy lakes, may all thy pleasures flow!

line_1: Wide as thy fancy, be thy spreading praise!
line_2: And long and lovely as thy walks, thy days!

line_1: And long and lovely as thy walks, thy days!
line_2: Wide as thy fancy, be thy spreading praise!
